WEBVTT

00:01.090 --> 00:10.443
In those days, a decree went out from Caesar, and so everyone went to their town to be registered.

00:10.563 --> 00:16.692
Joseph went out from Nazareth to the city of Bethlehem, along with Mary.

00:16.712 --> 00:22.821
And when they were there, it came time for her to give birth, and she gave birth to her firstborn son.

00:24.182 --> 00:26.706
Wrapped him in cloth and laid him in a manger.

00:31.650 --> 00:36.836
In the same region, shepherds were staying out in the field at night and keeping watch over their flock.

00:37.496 --> 00:43.443
Then an angel of the Lord stood before them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them.

00:44.304 --> 00:53.794
But the angel said to them, Do not be afraid, for I proclaim to you good news of great joy that will be for all the people.

00:53.814 --> 00:56.917
Today in the city of David, a Savior was born.

00:57.979 --> 01:01.202
For you who is the Messiah, the Lord,

01:13.442 --> 01:14.243
Give it up for our band.

01:14.944 --> 01:21.071
Yeah.

01:21.091 --> 01:23.735
You know, there's a lot that I love about the Christmas season.

01:23.775 --> 01:26.378
I love the music, like we just sang today.

01:26.398 --> 01:27.499
I love the movies.

01:28.020 --> 01:29.722
You know, I love the friends and the family.

01:29.742 --> 01:31.765
I love worshiping together on Christmas Eve.

01:31.825 --> 01:37.151
But I think what really sits underneath all of that is that feeling of anticipation.

01:37.952 --> 01:42.578
Now, I remember Christmas Eve when I was a kid and not being able to sleep.

01:42.690 --> 01:45.333
because I was so excited for Christmas morning.

01:45.353 --> 01:48.356
How many of you kids in here are excited for Christmas morning tomorrow?

01:48.496 --> 01:50.338
Yeah, all of you, absolutely.

01:51.479 --> 02:01.809
Well, this year, that anticipation, it began in our house much earlier than expected because in the first week of October, this book arrived at our house.

02:02.490 --> 02:03.951
Has anyone seen this book before?

02:03.971 --> 02:06.594
Maybe families, if you buy things from Amazon, okay.

02:07.094 --> 02:09.877
This is the Amazon Holiday Dash book.

02:10.418 --> 02:10.898
Now,

02:11.074 --> 02:23.932
Because of Amazon's desire to really serve families, they send you a book of toys that you don't sign up for and to get your kids ready for Christmas in October.

02:24.573 --> 02:28.479
So, and if you see in the bottom corner, there's over 600 toys and gift ideas in here.

02:28.519 --> 02:32.505
And what was really helpful was Amazon gave you a list in here.

02:32.565 --> 02:33.826
Yeah, little list.

02:34.147 --> 02:36.370
There's enough room for 11 items.

02:36.514 --> 02:37.435
Now I have two sons.

02:37.515 --> 02:39.277
They're nine and six years old.

02:39.338 --> 02:40.960
They didn't use this list.

02:41.060 --> 02:48.529
They circled the items because when they gave it back to us, there was 38 items in here circled.

02:49.390 --> 02:50.612
Yeah.

02:50.792 --> 02:56.239
But when this book arrived at our home 12 weeks ago, something changed.

02:57.180 --> 02:59.463
Didn't matter what our kids were thinking that day.

02:59.503 --> 03:03.088
It didn't matter who they were with or what plans they had.

03:03.148 --> 03:05.010
This book did something to them.

03:05.762 --> 03:09.026
It laser focused their attention on Christmas.

03:10.388 --> 03:12.111
It became the most important thing to them.

03:13.172 --> 03:18.520
And seeing our kids react that day to this book showing up in the mailbox, it reminded me of something that's true of all of us.

03:19.160 --> 03:23.607
And it's that our future hope impacts our present reality.

03:24.828 --> 03:33.160
What we look forward to, what we long for, our desire for things in the future, all those things, they change how we live our lives today.

03:33.921 --> 03:34.802
What we think about.

03:35.394 --> 03:39.099
the decisions that we make, what we give our time and our money and our attention to.

03:39.139 --> 03:45.187
The future hope of a job or of a career move that impacts your present work ethic.

03:45.808 --> 03:46.950
You work longer hours.

03:47.491 --> 03:48.752
You go above and beyond.

03:48.772 --> 03:52.417
You do things outside of your job descriptions so that you'll be noticed.

03:52.437 --> 03:54.100
Or maybe you'll get that job promotion.

03:54.881 --> 03:59.227
The future hope of retirement impacts how much you save and you budget right now.

04:00.128 --> 04:01.650
The future hope of a child.

04:01.954 --> 04:08.323
or of an adoption being finalized, or of a family that impacts your decisions that you make today, how you spend your time.

04:09.585 --> 04:13.370
We put our future hope in things that we believe will satisfy us.

04:14.151 --> 04:16.093
That will bring us joy and fulfillment.

04:17.215 --> 04:23.504
And God wired us in this way to be people who have longings who desire for more.

04:24.545 --> 04:30.994
But what's often challenging for us is when our future hopes seem so far away from our present reality.

04:31.810 --> 04:37.717
The book of Proverbs in the Old Testament is a book filled with wisdom and guidance for really how to live well.

04:37.777 --> 04:51.932
And it says this in Proverbs chapter 13, verse 12, it says this, the longer and longer we hope for something, the less we begin to believe that it'll actually ever come true.

04:53.054 --> 05:00.562
For the people of God, over hundreds of years, they had been waiting, waiting for a rescuer to arrive in the world and to redeem them.

05:00.930 --> 05:08.818
Since the very beginning of everything, they had been waiting for a Messiah, a chosen one, one who had come and who had set things right with the world.

05:09.819 --> 05:16.746
There were prophecies that God had given them about this Messiah in the past, messages that God had given them about what was going to happen in the future.

05:16.786 --> 05:18.188
We see these in the Old Testament.

05:18.708 --> 05:22.813
Psalm 132 speaks of a Messiah who had come from the line of David.

05:23.413 --> 05:28.018
Isaiah chapter 9 tells us that a child would be born who would be called wonderful counselor.

05:28.290 --> 05:31.194
mighty God, everlasting Father and Prince of Peace.

05:31.995 --> 05:39.646
And then later in Isaiah 53, it speaks of a suffering servant that would bring us peace by taking our sins onto himself.

05:41.048 --> 05:46.696
All of these prophecies, they shaped the future hope that the people of God possessed.

05:47.838 --> 05:56.370
But as time passed, hundreds and hundreds of years, that Messiah still hadn't arrived, and that hope was delayed

05:56.802 --> 05:58.204
further and further away.

05:59.426 --> 06:02.470
But one night in Bethlehem, everything changed.

06:03.371 --> 06:06.255
Luke chapter two, verse eight says this.

06:06.976 --> 06:13.986
In the same region, shepherds were staying out in the fields and keeping watch at night over their flock that an angel of the Lord stood before them.

06:14.747 --> 06:17.251
And the glory of the Lord shone around them and they were terrified.

06:17.751 --> 06:20.655
But the angel said to them, don't be afraid for look.

06:20.956 --> 06:25.362
I proclaim to you good news of great joy that will be for all the people.

06:25.698 --> 06:28.802
Today in the city of David, a Savior was born for you.

06:29.303 --> 06:31.185
Who is the Messiah, the Lord?

06:32.567 --> 06:36.152
On an ordinary night in Bethlehem, some shepherds were just doing what they did every night.

06:36.172 --> 06:38.195
They were watching over their sheep.

06:39.076 --> 06:45.084
But an angel shows up, and the glory of the Lord shines around them, causing these shepherds to be terrified.

06:45.705 --> 06:49.710
And the angel shares with them the most important message they would ever hear in their life.

06:50.591 --> 06:55.538
The angel said this, I proclaim to you, good news of great

06:55.778 --> 06:56.199
joy.

06:58.022 --> 07:01.828
There's nothing better than getting good news from someone, right?

07:02.970 --> 07:05.214
Think about the moments in your life that this has happened to you.

07:06.015 --> 07:06.997
You got the job.

07:08.098 --> 07:08.940
You got accepted.

07:09.941 --> 07:10.923
You're cancer-free.

07:12.065 --> 07:12.666
It's a boy.

07:12.706 --> 07:14.148
It's a girl.

07:14.209 --> 07:22.322
This night, an angel tells the shepherds, something has happened in Bethlehem that is good news of great

07:22.530 --> 07:25.794
But this news they were about to hear, it doesn't just impact them.

07:25.834 --> 07:27.796
It is much bigger in scale.

07:28.798 --> 07:32.702
It's good news of great joy that will be for all the people.

07:34.224 --> 07:38.269
What happened that night that the shepherds were told about, it went far beyond just them.

07:38.309 --> 07:41.673
It was good news on a global scale.

07:42.334 --> 07:47.941
It was more than just the shepherds, more than just the people of Bethlehem, more than just the people, the Jewish people.

07:48.441 --> 07:52.466
It was good news of great joy for all people.

07:53.602 --> 08:00.855
Everyone in the world, in every time, in every place would be impacted by what happened on this night.

08:02.097 --> 08:03.500
And this was the news.

08:04.602 --> 08:10.412
Today, in the city of David, a Savior was born for you, who is the Messiah, the Lord.

08:11.895 --> 08:18.066
On that night, the one they had been waiting for, a Messiah, an anointed one, was born.

08:19.394 --> 08:31.251
Over hundreds of years before this, the Jewish people, they would gather, they would worship, they would open the scriptures and they would pray and they would look forward to this event that a Messiah would come for them.

08:32.733 --> 08:41.145
After the shepherds received this news, they run to Bethlehem to see Mary and Joseph and to see this baby with their own eyes that the angel had told them about.

08:41.946 --> 08:47.474
And what they see is this a normal, healthy baby boy, born to two ordinary people.

08:48.450 --> 08:51.474
But after they see Jesus, look at what they do, verse 20.

08:52.095 --> 08:59.686
The shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things they had seen and heard, which were just as they had been told.

09:01.549 --> 09:04.653
After everything that happens that night, they go back to their sheep.

09:05.514 --> 09:07.477
This was their life's work, right?

09:07.657 --> 09:10.481
The next day they woke up and they were still shepherds.

09:11.643 --> 09:16.530
But even though they went back to their normal lives, they were not the same people.

09:17.506 --> 09:22.151
These ordinary shepherds experienced the grace of their extraordinary God.

09:23.392 --> 09:29.178
They got to see the Messiah, the object of their hope, the one God had promised them.

09:30.940 --> 09:33.983
See, for the shepherds, the news they heard that night, it changed them.

09:34.423 --> 09:35.585
It changed everything.

09:36.746 --> 09:44.594
Their future hope was impacted by their present reality that a Messiah had been born for them.

09:46.178 --> 09:51.404
In a way, we're all like those shepherds 2,000 years ago that the angel spoke to.

09:52.665 --> 09:55.868
Our future hope impacts our present reality.

09:57.170 --> 09:59.592
Those future hopes that we have, they fill our minds.

10:00.333 --> 10:04.417
We often think of them as a finish line that we're working toward, right?

10:04.437 --> 10:05.679
That we make decisions about.

10:06.459 --> 10:12.626
And sometimes, by the grace of God, those hopes become a future reality.

10:13.538 --> 10:17.542
What we look forward to with anticipation, they actually show up in front of us.

10:18.703 --> 10:19.644
You get the job.

10:20.585 --> 10:21.867
The situation works out.

10:22.467 --> 10:23.348
You have a child.

10:24.209 --> 10:28.954
You get what you circled in the Amazon holiday dash book, right?

10:30.315 --> 10:38.303
Earlier I read Proverbs 1312 about hope, delayed making a heart sick, but I actually only read the first half of the verse.

10:39.104 --> 10:40.786
The rest of the verse says this.

10:41.058 --> 10:47.784
Hope delayed makes the heart sick, but desire fulfilled as a tree of life.

10:49.907 --> 10:52.970
Having our desires fulfilled, it's often a life-giving thing.

10:54.131 --> 10:56.213
It can bring happiness.

10:57.494 --> 11:07.003
But while it's encouraging to get what we hope for, we can often find that we're disappointed when what we had hoped for, what we had worked so hard to get.

11:07.043 --> 11:10.066
It doesn't do for us what we were hoping it would.

11:11.458 --> 11:15.582
Now I have some great memories of getting what I wanted for Christmas as a kid.

11:15.602 --> 11:24.131
I remember waking up Christmas morning and unwrapping the toy or the game or the model or whatever it was that I poured over in this magazine.

11:25.252 --> 11:28.896
And while it did bring momentary happiness and fun, it never lasted.

11:30.357 --> 11:39.186
It faded over time because those things that I desired, those things I hoped for, they could never satisfy the deeper need that I had.

11:40.354 --> 11:43.978
the deeper need that every single one of us have in our humanity.

11:45.660 --> 11:47.703
Today, we're all in various stages of life.

11:48.724 --> 11:53.950
We have different desires, different longings, different aspirations, and all of those future hopes.

11:54.311 --> 11:58.436
They change how we live today in the present.

11:59.637 --> 12:03.622
They change how we spend our time, our money, our energy.

12:04.623 --> 12:10.130
And many of us are convinced that if we just get that thing, that'll be it.

12:10.818 --> 12:17.086
We'll have what we need, but even when we do, we still find ourselves longing.

12:18.147 --> 12:22.752
Our hope just moves on to something else, because there's always something else, right?

12:23.513 --> 12:26.937
The next job, the next purchase, the next experience.

12:28.439 --> 12:37.330
And this is because even though each one of us are different in where our hopes lie, we all share one longing that is deeper than any other.

12:38.434 --> 12:45.962
a longing that we may not even realize that we have, a universal ache that only has one solution.

12:47.344 --> 12:52.890
And that ache is that all of us were made to experience life with God.

12:54.331 --> 12:59.557
Ecclesiastes 3 verse 11 says that God has set eternity into the hearts of mankind.

13:00.618 --> 13:07.826
That every person who has ever lived has this eternal longing that only God can satisfy

13:08.354 --> 13:15.444
But we often try and fill it with other things, with substitutes, more stuff, more comfort, more experiences.

13:16.425 --> 13:20.511
But those things can never satisfy us in the way that our Creator only can.

13:21.993 --> 13:26.099
There was a theologian and a philosopher who lived about 300 years after Jesus.

13:26.139 --> 13:27.060
His name was Augustine.

13:27.721 --> 13:30.765
And he described that universal ache that we have in this way.

13:31.506 --> 13:34.450
He says, you have made us for yourself, O Lord.

13:35.211 --> 13:37.234
And our hearts are restless.

13:37.826 --> 13:39.508
until they rest in you.

13:42.071 --> 13:54.026
Regardless of where those future hopes that we have, regardless of where those lie, we all share this restlessness of the heart that is only meant for God to satisfy.

13:54.787 --> 13:58.572
And Christmas is the celebration of that need being met.

14:00.014 --> 14:03.538
It's the story of future hope becoming present reality.

14:04.322 --> 14:10.071
The story of God coming near and fulfilling the prophecies that he spoke over hundreds and hundreds of years.

14:11.412 --> 14:23.811
It's the story of our greatest need being met by our great savior, Jesus, our Messiah, this universal ache that we have.

14:24.993 --> 14:26.996
It can't be satisfied on our own.

14:27.316 --> 14:28.658
And that's because of our sin.

14:29.410 --> 14:38.602
our failure to reflect the image of God and our nature, attitude and our actions, no matter how good we are, no matter how hard we try, we cannot do it on our own.

14:39.784 --> 14:42.467
And that is why the Christmas story matters.

14:43.849 --> 14:50.058
Because this baby born in Bethlehem would grow up and he'd lived the perfect life that none of us could.

14:51.379 --> 14:53.062
Jesus was without sin.

14:54.003 --> 14:59.410
He was perfect, but he would go to the cross for sinners, the imperfect,

14:59.874 --> 15:00.515
for all of us.

15:01.836 --> 15:11.968
And his death for our sins would make a way for us to experience life with God, for that restlessness to be satisfied in the forgiveness of sin that comes by faith.

15:13.549 --> 15:22.139
Three days after he would die, Jesus resurrected to prove that he was God and that sin and Satan and death would be conquered forever.

15:24.622 --> 15:28.146
Think about yourself today, this Christmas Eve.

15:29.314 --> 15:32.138
Is your heart restless today?

15:33.700 --> 15:34.521
Where is your hope?

15:36.144 --> 15:38.267
What are you trusting in that will satisfy you?

15:39.809 --> 15:47.079
While many of these desires may be for good things, don't expect them to satisfy for you what only God can.

15:48.942 --> 15:50.965
Choose to follow Christ today.

15:52.507 --> 15:54.770
Celebrate like the shepherds did that night.

15:55.170 --> 16:00.840
Glorify and praise God for what you have seen and from what you have heard in the scriptures today.

16:02.162 --> 16:09.234
Celebrate who Jesus is, what he's done, the beautiful gift of salvation that he offers you today.

16:11.217 --> 16:15.565
If you've never done that, that salvation, it comes in one way.

16:16.266 --> 16:21.074
It comes by faith, by trusting in Jesus, what he's done.

16:21.474 --> 16:30.046
by recognizing that you need saving from your sin, that you cannot do it on your own, but that Jesus has done it for you.

16:31.769 --> 16:49.554
If you are a Christian today, maybe you've known that, you heard that years ago, choose to treasure that gift fresh today, that your identity is secure as a child of God, that you are secure

16:49.954 --> 16:59.243
because of your faith in Christ, that your greatest need was met by a great savior, Jesus, our Messiah.

16:59.263 --> 17:11.334
And finally this, that our future hope became a present reality on Christmas, that today in the city of David, a savior was born for you.

17:12.215 --> 17:14.317
Who is the Messiah, the Lord?

17:15.518 --> 17:15.979
Let's pray.

17:17.480 --> 17:19.602
Heavenly Father, we do just thank you

17:20.322 --> 17:22.444
We thank you so much for that gift.

17:25.327 --> 17:31.134
God, you have made us in a way where we long for things.

17:31.854 --> 17:33.556
We work hard, we have desires.

17:34.758 --> 17:35.959
And God, that's intentional.

17:36.019 --> 17:43.407
Lord, you made us in this way to be a people who aren't satisfied.

17:44.768 --> 17:50.034
And God, that is because we all have eternity set in our hearts.

17:50.626 --> 18:00.740
Lord, you have made us in a way that those aches and those longings, they will not be satisfied by anything we acquire or anything we experience except for you.

18:02.703 --> 18:03.904
God, we thank you for Christmas.

18:04.906 --> 18:16.722
The story of you coming to earth for us, sending a Messiah, an anointed one that would bridge the gap that we have because of our sin.

18:18.882 --> 18:28.051
Lord, we're grateful tonight for the opportunity just to rest in that truth, that you came near, that you made a way for us and that you love us.

18:30.037 --> 18:32.786
In Jesus' name that we pray, amen.

